---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - Third Screen">
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-[#0a0a0a] px-6 py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl">
      <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-white/40 hover:text-white/60 transition-colors mb-8" style="font-family:Inter,system-ui,sans-serif;">
        &larr; Back to home
      </a>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight mb-2" style="font-family:Inter,system-ui,sans-serif;">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-white/40 text-sm mb-10" style="font-family:Inter,system-ui,sans-serif;">Last updated: March 27, 2026</p>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-white/70 text-sm leading-relaxed" style="font-family:Inter,system-ui,sans-serif;">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-lg mb-3">What Third Screen Is</h2>
          <p>
            Third Screen is a personal dashboard application that displays your schedule, tasks, notes, health data, and music in a single glanceable view. It is available as a web application and a desktop application.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Data Storage</h2>
          <p>
            Third Screen is local-first. Your data (tasks, notes, calendar events, calorie logs, medicine schedules) is stored locally on your device by default. No account is required to use the core features.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            When you choose to connect external services (Google Calendar, Spotify), authentication tokens are stored locally on your device to maintain your connection. We do not store your passwords.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p>Third Screen integrates with the following services when you choose to connect them:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-3 space-y-2">
            <li><strong class="text-white">Google Calendar</strong> - We request read-only access to your calendar events to display them on your dashboard. We use Google's OAuth 2.0 for authentication.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-white">Spotify</strong> - We request access to your playback state to display currently playing music and control playback. We use Spotify's OAuth with PKCE for authentication.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-white">LRCLib</strong> - We fetch song lyrics from LRCLib (lrclib.net), an open-source lyrics database. Only the song title, artist, and album name are sent to retrieve lyrics.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Data We Do Not Collect</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
            <li>We do not collect personal information</li>
            <li>We do not use analytics or tracking</li>
            <li>We do not sell or share your data with third parties</li>
            <li>We do not serve advertisements</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Open Source</h2>
          <p>
            Third Screen is open source. You can inspect the complete source code at
            <a href="https://github.com/ericvaish/thirdscreen" target="_blank" class="text-[#3b82f6] hover:underline">github.com/ericvaish/thirdscreen</a>
            to verify exactly what the application does with your data.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Contact</h2>
          <p>
            If you have questions about this privacy policy, you can reach the developer at
            <a href="https://ericvaish.com" target="_blank" class="text-[#3b82f6] hover:underline">ericvaish.com</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
